      "matters": "ACCOUNTING PETITION RE: ACCOUNTING #1, REPORT, FEES, FINAL DISTRIBUTION<br>Off Calendar Jan-09-2007 Granted Per Written Order<br>MINI MINUTES: Appearances: Raymond Levy (Personal Representative); Laura Goldin (Counsel for Suzette Safdie, Third-Party Beneficiary).<br><br>Ms. Goldin appeared to contest the proposed final distribution to David Katsky in light of a Family Court Order and Writ against Mr. Katsky and in favor of her client. After some discussion, the Court granted the Accounting Petition and granted the final Distribution Petition, amending the same to pay David Katsky's distribution to Ms. Goldin as Trustee for Ms. Safdie.<br><br>Further discussion ensued with respect to Mr. Levy's request for extraordinary fees, the Court being of the opinion that certain of the fees were statutory services and concerns that the hourly rate were excessive. This matter was taken under submission.<br><br>Judicial Officer: Judge John Dearman; Reporter: Katy Bersamin CSR #11722; Court Examiner: Tim Kneis; Bailiff: Deputy Mizota; Clerk: R. Michael Diles.",
